<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles/howto.css" />
  <script defer src="./scripts/about.js"></script>
  <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/7daf78b674.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <title>ENJOYWINTER</title>
</head>

<body>
  <header id="navigation_bar">

    <div class="logo_section">
      <div id="logo_wrapper">
        <a href="./main.jsp"><i id="logo_img" class="fa-solid fa-snowflake"></i></a>
      </div>
      <a href="./main.jsp" id="logo">Winjoy</a>
    </div>
  </header>


  <section>

    <div class="horizontal-scroll">

      <a class="step_card">
        <div class="step_item_card">
          <img src="./assets/images/howtoski/step1.jpg" alt="" />
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h4 class="title">Step1</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h5 class="title">Learn the Proper Ski Stance</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h6 class="title">
              - Stand relatively tall with your feet about shoulder-width apart.<br> <br>
              - Flex your ankles and tilt your shins forward.<br> <br>
              - Keep your shoulders slightly in front of your hips with weight <br>
              centered over both feet.<br> <br>
              - Keep your arms slightly out in front and off to the side. <br> <br>
              - Hold your poles with the tips pointed back, behind your feet.<br> <br>
              - Look toward where you're going, not down at your skis.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a class="step_card">
        <div class="step_item_card">
          <img src="./assets/images/howtoski/step2_1.jpg" alt="" />
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h4 class="title">Step2</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h5 class="title">How to Glide on Skis</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h6 class="title">
              After clicking into your skis, <br> <br>
              you'll learn what it's like to balance and move on skis. <br> <br>
              Gliding on flat terrain is one of the first movements you'll make.<br> <br>
              - Push off with your ski poles (one on each side).<br> <br>
              - Flex your ankles.<br> <br>
              - Keep your shins tilted forward and your weight centered <br>
              over your feet as you move with your skis.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a class="step_card">
        <div class="step_item_card">
          <img src="./assets/images/howtoski/step2_2.jpg" alt="" />
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h4 class="title">Step2</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h5 class="title">How to Glide on Skis</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h6 class="title">
             Next, try gliding down a gentle hill. <br> <br>
             This gets you familiar with balancing on skis <br><br>
             that are sliding down a slope.<br> <br> <br>
             - Point your skis downhill, push off with your poles and glide <br>
             to a natural stop.<br> <br>
             - Practice gliding and balancing over short distances and <br>
             on small slopes or inclines.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a class="step_card">
        <div class="step_item_card">
          <img src="./assets/images/howtoski/step3.jpg" alt="" />
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h4 class="title">Step3</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h5 class="title">How to side-step uphill:</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h6 class="title">
              - Position your skis parallel and face across the slope, <br>
              perpendicular to the fall line (the most direct path down).<br><br>
              - Tilt your skis slightly towards the slope.<br><br>
              - Push off with your downhill ski and step sideways up the hill<br>
              with your uphill ski. Then bring the other ski parallel to it.<br><br>
              - Take small steps and lean your lower legs into the slope, <br>
              not your butt or shoulders.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a class="step_card">
        <div class="step_item_card">
          <img src="./assets/images/howtoski/step4.jpg" alt="" />
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h4 class="title">Step4</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h5 class="title">How to Ski in a Wedge</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h6 class="title">
              - Practice a wedge stance on flat ground, ski tips close, <br>
              tails apart.<br><br>
              - Glide down a gentle slope in a wedge, stopping naturally.<br><br>
              - On a hill, form a ski triangle to control speed; wider <br>
              for slower, narrower for faster.<br><br>
              - Stop with a wide wedge, start with a narrow one and poles.<br><br>
              - Focus on consistent speed and stopping.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a class="step_card">
        <div class="step_item_card">
          <img src="./assets/images/howtoski/step5.jpg" alt="" />
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h4 class="title">Step5</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h5 class="title">How to do a Wedge Turn</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="step_card_text">
            <h6 class="title">
              - To steer while gliding in a wedge, twist your legs <br>
              to direct the skis, maintaining the wedge shape.<br><br>
              - Shift more weight onto the outside/downhill ski to turn: <br>
              left foot for a right turn, right foot for a left turn.<br><br>
              - To stop, turn until you're positioned across the slope.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

    </div>

  </section>

</body>

</html>